This cover carried in Plane No. 10 of
Scouting Squadron Forty-Two attached to
the U. S. S. Ranger which participated in
search for the ill fated Crew of Patrol
Squadron Eighteen Plane No. 7 under Com-
mand of Lieutenant Charles E. Signer, U.S.
Navy. Many Planes which participated in
this search including the one in which this
cover was carried participated in the Navys
search for Amelia Earhart around Howland
Island, in June, 1937.

properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, carried on Plane No. 10 of Scouting Squadron Forty-two during mass naval search for crew of Patrol Squadron Eighteen Plane No. 7; white envelope with red and blue diagonally striped border and printed certificate at left; postmarked U.S.S. Ranger on March 31, 1938 with “Off North Coast Kauai” cancellation mark; backstamp: April 1, 1938, U.S.S. Ranger with “Lahaina Roads-T.H.” cancellation mark.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “March 1938, massive navy search mission”, and two black and white photographs of U.S.S. Ranger and airplane.
